  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For awareness raising campaign targeting rural peasants, farmers, women, indigenous people, consumers, policymakers, and other stakeholders on the dangers of the use of hazardous pesticides in India&apos;s agricultural sector, with special attention given to endosulfan. The project will include array of public events, including community workshops, film and photo screenings, rallies, and public hearings. Sahanivasa will collect testimony and signatures from agriculture-affected communities, to be compiled and submitted in petition form to appropriate government agencies. This campaign will be undertaken in collaboration with the Andhra Pradesh Vyavasaya Vruthidarula Union and Pesticide Action Network-Asia Pacific</narrative>
